  "title": "Assistant Project Manager (Landscape / Construction) #79866",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Wholesales & Retails Trade</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Assistant Project Manager (Landscape / Construction)</strong></li><li>Working Location: Bedok</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Monday-Friday, 8AM – 5PM)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Variable Bonus + Medical Benefits</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in planning, coordination, and execution of landscape projects.</li><li>Support project operations, including manpower, material, and equipment allocation.</li><li>Prepare and manage project documentation such as RFIs, change orders, progress claims, and project close-out reports.</li><li>Coordinate with clients, consultants, subcontractors, and suppliers to ensure smooth project delivery.</li><li>Conduct site inspections to monitor work quality, progress, and safety compliance.</li><li>Prepare and manage project documentation, reports, and claims.</li><li>Assist in budgeting, cost monitoring, and procurement schedules.</li><li>Ensure compliance with environmental, safety, and quality standards.</li><li>Support tender preparation and other ad-hoc project tasks as assigned.</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc duties assigned by Management.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Landscape Architecture, Horticulture, Civil Engineering, Project Management, or related field.</li><li>2 years of relevant experience in landscape or construction project management.</li><li>Knowledge of landscape construction, horticultural practices, and site management.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office; MS Project or AutoCAD knowledge preferred.</li><li>Able to read technical drawings and manage multiple stakeholders.</li><li>Risk Assessment Management Level 2 certification and Class 3 driving licence are advantages.</li><li>Proactive, organized, and able to work independently in a fast-paced environment.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79866 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
